<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="excited-adj">excited <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ɪk'saɪtɪd/    美 /ɪk'saɪtɪd/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>兴奋的；激动的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The children were <strong>excited at</strong> the thought of the journey. 
孩子们一想到旅行就很兴奋。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Children are <strong>excited about</strong> playing with their new toys.
孩子们对玩新玩具感到很兴奋。</p><footer>2014 全国</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I'm very excited (that) we're going to New York.
我们要去纽约了，对此我感到非常兴奋。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) excited + to do sth：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I am very excited to have got an e-mail from you. 
收到你的电子邮件，我非常激动。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>At the age of twelve, I got a nice bike as a birthday gift. So excited was I that I couldn't wait to try my hand at riding it.
十二岁时，作为生日礼物我得到了一辆不错的自行车。我兴奋不已，以至于迫不及待地想骑一下。</p><footer>2014 福建</footer></div></div>